ec3 database download
The Embodied Carbon in Construction Calculator (EC3) database is a free, cloud-based tool and is not typically downloaded as a standalone offline file. Instead, you access the data through the official platform or via integrations with design software. 
How to Access the EC3 Database
Web Access: Register for a free account at BuildingTransparency.org to search and compare over 100,000 digitized Environmental Product Declarations (EPDs).
Reporting & Exports: Within the web tool, you can download Summary Reports (often in CSV or PDF) of specific building projects you have created.
Software Integrations: You can "download" or connect the database directly into construction workflows using plugins:
tallyCAT: A free Revit plug-in that synchronizes material quantities with the EC3 database.
Autodesk Construction Cloud: Integration available through the Autodesk App Store.
Procore: Access reports directly via the Procore Marketplace integration. 
Alternative Embodied Carbon Downloads
If you require a fully downloadable offline database for carbon factors, consider the Inventory of Carbon & Energy (ICE) database, which is available as a free Excel/CSV download from Circular Ecology. 
